<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="87" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[1282,2268,2708,3163]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">
Australian Carboniferous species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" box="[1967,2266,2708,2748]" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteoninidae" genus="Girtyspira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[1967,2266,2708,2748]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">Girtyspira inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1282,1363,2756,2795]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from Swains Gully.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[1282,2268,2708,3163]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">
Remarks. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kollmann, H. &amp; E. L. Yochelson" box="[1524,2067,2801,2840]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" pagination="207 - 220" refId="ref26365" refString="Kollmann, H. A &amp; E. L. Yochelson, 1976. Survey of Paleozoic gastropods possibly belonging to the subclass Opisthobranchia. Naturhistorisches Museum in Wien Annalen 80: 207 - 220." type="journal article" year="1976">Kollmann &amp; Yochelson (1976)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1936" box="[1283,1481,2847,2886]" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteoninidae" genus="Girtyspira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1481,2847,2886]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">Girtyspira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the subulitoideans to the opisthobranchs, on the basis of a deviated protoconch and sutural ramp. 
<bibRefCitation author="Erwin, D. H." box="[1619,1851,2939,2979]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" pagination="566 - 575" refId="ref25122" refString="Erwin, D. H., 1988. Permian gastropoda of the southwestern United States: Cerithiacea, Acteonacea, and Pyramidellacea. Journal of Paleontology 62 (4), 566 - 575." type="journal article" year="1988">Erwin (1988)</bibRefCitation>
also placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1936" box="[2094,2267,2939,2979]" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteoninidae" genus="Girtyspira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[2094,2267,2939,2979]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">Girtyspira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the opisthobranchs. The studied form 
<taxonomicName authority="Yoo, 1994" authorityName="Yoo" authorityYear="1994" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteoninidae" genus="Girtyspira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coenogastropoda incertae sedis" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="inflata" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="87">Girtyspira inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1417,1494,3031,3070]" pageId="24" pageNumber="87" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a deviated protoconch, but not seen clearly as heterostrophic. It is, here, retained in the Subulitoidea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
